<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger.GetLoggerChildScope" Title="GetLoggerChildScope method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger">ILogger</PageRef> ->
    GetLoggerChildScope
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>GetLoggerChildScope</TypeRef> method creates a new logger object for a scope below the current logger scope.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        The standard <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Logger">Logger</PageRef> implementation joins parent and child scopes using a period, so a child named <TypeRef>Render</TypeRef> below <TypeRef>Application</TypeRef> becomes <TypeRef>Application.Render</TypeRef>.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[ILogger::unique_ptr GetLoggerChildScope(const std::string& childScopeName) const;]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="const std::string&amp;" Name="childScopeName">The child scope name to append to the current scope.</ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
    <SubSection Title="Return value">
      <ReturnValue Type="ILogger!cobalt.logging.ILogger">
        A new <TypeRef>ILogger</TypeRef> object for the child scope, wrapped in <TypeRef>ILogger::unique_ptr</TypeRef>.
      </ReturnValue>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger.GetScope">ILogger.GetScope</PageRefListEntry>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager.GetLogger">LogManager.GetLogger</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
